Text: The final week!I very much enjoyed the work from the past week as it has provided a rich learning experience regarding packaging project work.
I felt we were able to complete the project to a reasonable standard, much better than what we initially expected.
We were able to finish the content on the website and organise it in a much more sophisticated way than what they already have.
We were able to achieve this with the use of plugins which we all became familiar with during the website development process.
I now feel comfortable using wordpress developers to make a website and utilize plugins to achieve the desired functions on the website.
A downfall which I didn't expect from the website is that utilizing plugins can cost money.
This is not ideal being students learning about wordpress with no access to funding to support the development of this project.
Another downfall is that the website has not been performing very well regarding its loading speed.
This is likely due to many plugins being used also, which overall slows down the speed to which the website is responsive.
This is a problem as website loading speed is a key specification for good website design and recognising this issue late in the project has meant that we were unable to overcome this.
If I were to develop another wordpress website, I would utilize plugins that do not impact the loading page speed and develop more code rather than being so dependent on plugins.
Overall I have really enjoyed this project.
I have felt in control of my skills and like I have been able to contribute to the development work without feeling out of place or less technically capable than my team.

I have learnt about good website design, the process for requirements elicitation through user stories, using tools to make high fidelity prototypes and also using wordpress developer with both plugins and coding.
